snippet.title: Meet The $10 Million Dollar Tennis Player Who's Never Won A Title
snippet.description:
By practically any way of accounting, 26-year-old Alejandro Davidovich Fokina is one of the best tennis players in the world. The Spaniard, currently ranked No. 15, has won 43 matches this year—the sixth-most of any player, including five wins over top-10 opponents (tied for the most after Carlos Alcaraz and Jannik Sinner).

With a win in the second round of the 2025 Paris Masters over Arthur Cazaux on Wednesday, he surpassed eight figures in prize money over his career.

And yet he’s never won an ATP singles title.

snippet.title: Badenoch Clarifies: Tories Won't Deport Legally Settled People - Immigration Policy Update
snippet.description:
Kemi Badenoch clarifies the Conservative Party's stance on immigration, stating they will NOT retrospectively deport legally settled individuals. This comes after confusion sparked by Katie Lam's comments about revoking indefinite leave to remain (ILR). We break down the key points:
 Badenoch's reassurance on retrospective changes to ILR.
 The circumstances under which ILR can be revoked (criminal activity).
 The impact of potentially leaving the European Convention on Human Rights (ECHR) on immigration policy.
 Labour's concerns and Badenoch's response regarding benefits and maternity pay.
 Analysis of the internal Conservative Party divisions on immigration policy.
